explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach with two pointers (left and right) to traverse the string s. It maintains a count of characters in the current window and in the string t. When the window contains all characters of t, it tries to minimize the window by moving the left pointer. The time complexity is O(m + n) as we are traversing the string s once. The space complexity is O(n) for storing the counts of characters in the window and in the string t.

